.TH CREATESIGNERKEY 9 "" "" "Inferno Security Modules and Utilities"
.PP
.SH NAME
createsignerkey \- command to create signer key on authentication server
.SH SYNOPSYS
.IP
.EX
lib/createsignerkey name\-of\-owner [size\-in\-bits] [file]
.EE
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
The createsignerkey command creates a private key for the string supplied as the first command argument.
The size of the key is given by the second argument (default: 512 bits) and the result is stored in the file named by the third argument (default: /keydb/signerkey).
.PP
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
